This paper deals with mechanism design for combinatorial auctions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and algorithms (cs.DS). The focus is on auctions with submodular bidders, which is a specific type of valuation function commonly studied in algorithmic game theory (cs.AI). The paper also discusses approximation guarantees and optimization, which are topics in theoretical computer science (cs.THE) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper introduces a notion of competitive markets, which is a topic in economics (cs.EC).
